◆ max_contiguous_dir_credits

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::max_contiguous_dir_credits

Directed credits are allocated to a scheduling domain in a contiguous chunk, because each pool must be configured with a contiguous chunk of credits. This is the largest available contiguous range of directed credits.

◆ max_contiguous_ldb_credits

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::max_contiguous_ldb_credits

Load-balanced credits are allocated to a scheduling domain in a contiguous chunk, because each pool must be configured with a contiguous chunk of credits. This is the largest available contiguous range of load-balanced credits.

◆ max_contiguous_ldb_event_state_entries

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::max_contiguous_ldb_event_state_entries

Load-balanced event state storage is allocated to a scheduling domain in a contiguous chunk, because each port must be configured with a contiguous chunk of state entries. This is the largest available contiguous range of load-balanced event state entries.

◆ num_credit_pools

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_credit_pools

Number of available credit pools. For most cases, one pool per scheduling domain is recommended. In this case, all the domain's producer ports will pull from the same reservoir of credits when sending to an event queue. Using multiple pools in a scheduling domain raises the possibility of credit starvation deadlock (

See also
dlb_send for details on avoiding deadlock).

◆ num_credits

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_credits

Number of available credits. A credit is spent when a port enqueues an event to a queue.

◆ num_dir_credit_pools

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_dir_credit_pools

Number of available directed credit pools. For most cases, one pool per scheduling domain is recommended. In this case, all the domain's producer ports will pull from the same reservoir of credits when sending to directed queues. Using multiple pools in a scheduling domain raises the possibility of credit starvation deadlock (

See also
dlb_send for details on avoiding deadlock).

◆ num_dir_credits

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_dir_credits

Number of available directed credits. A directed credit is spent when a port enqueues to a directed queue.

◆ num_dir_ports

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_dir_ports

Number of available directed ports. A directed port receives events from a single (directed) queue, and can send events to any queue in its scheduling domain.

◆ num_ldb_credit_pools

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_ldb_credit_pools

Number of available load-balanced credit pools. For most cases, one pool per scheduling domain is recommended. In this case, all the domain's producer ports will pull from the same reservoir of credits when sending to load-balanced queues. Using multiple pools in a scheduling domain raises the possibility of credit starvation deadlock (

See also
dlb_send for details on avoiding deadlock).

◆ num_ldb_credits

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_ldb_credits

Number of available load-balanced credits. A load-balanced credit is spent when a port enqueues to a load-balanced queue.

◆ num_ldb_event_state_entries

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_ldb_event_state_entries

Load-balanced event state entries. Each event scheduled to a load-balanced port uses an event state entry until the application releases it. The scheduling domain's event state entries are statically divided among its ports.

◆ num_ldb_ports

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_ldb_ports

Number of available load-balanced ports. A load-balanced port can link to up to 8 load-balanced queues to receive events, and can send events to any queue in its scheduling domain.

◆ num_ldb_ports_per_cos

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_ldb_ports_per_cos[4]

Number of load-balanced ports belonging to each of the four classes-of-service. The sum of this array is equal to num_ldb_ports.

This field is not valid if the device doesn't support load-balanced port classes of service (indicated by the port_cos capability flag).

◆ num_ldb_queues

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_ldb_queues

Number of available load-balanced queues. Each event sent to a load-balanced queue is scheduled among its linked ports according to one of three scheduling types: atomic, ordered, or unordered.

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_sched_domains

Number of available scheduling domains

uint32_t dlb_resources_t::num_sn_slots[2]
